                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13641" author="tdiggins" created="Thu, 23 Jun 2005 20:52:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ought to add that this problem only occurred when I was using file: urls. Now that I have changed to using only classpath resource urls (bare paths), the problem has gone away!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore suggest adding this warning to the javadocs of AbstractDependencyInjectionSpringContextTests  and/or ref for testing (e.g. 21.2.7) in eclipse:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Note: for the time being at least, use only classpath resource urls when doing Integration tests from within eclipse (or you may have false failures when changing context locations)&quot; &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14211" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2005 21:22:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added a warning to AbstractDependencyInjectionSpringContextTests. And as I&apos;ve just stated in the forum, the exception caused is already a nicer NotWritablePropertyException since Spring 1.2.3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of course, we still don&apos;t know the root cause of this, but I suppose it&apos;s an Eclipse classloading issue rather than anything in Spring itself. Nevertheless, I&apos;ll close the issue for the time being, as we have a solution that works: loading resources from the classpath.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
